  "text": "In addition to the vitality of intestinal wall, Alshawi et Al12 proposed the following management options based on the stage of pregnancy: in the first trimester, and in recurrent cases in the second trimester, colonoscopic detorsion and rectal decompression are performed [CITATION_1] . Sigmoid colectomy is recommended in the second trimester, because endoscopic decompression is associated with high recurrence rate of volvulus, and operating in the second trimester is associated with lower miscarriage rate than the first [CITATION_2] . In the third trimester, endoscopic decompression is performed until fetal maturity, when elective labor followed by sigmoidectomy provides the final treatment.",
